This paper involves the analysis of user-generated content and the application of network analysis methods, which are commonly used in the fields of social media and information retrieval. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves the use of data mining techniques to uncover patterns in the data, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) or cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing). Additionally, the paper focuses on movie lists and their characteristics, which could fall under cs.SOC (Social and Information Networks) or cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
